SIMPLE: peccant
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peccant
<hw>Pec"cant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peccans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>peccare</ets> to
sin: cf. F. <ets>peccant</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sinning; guilty
of transgression; criminal; <as>as, <ex>peccant</ex> angels</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Morbid; corrupt; <as>as, <ex>peccant</ex>
humors</as>.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Wrong; defective; faulty.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ayliffe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peccant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Peccant
<hw>Pec"cant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An offender.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Whitlock.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peccantly</ent>⟦br⟧
